						<summary>

						<p>On the back side pillar in Survey No. 20.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraphy may be assigned to the 12th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Peeled off at the end. It seems to record the consecration of some deity by Katyadēsati, in the village Kadamiṭlapūmḍi which belonges to the god Śrīkaṁṭhīśvara of Kaṁcheṟvula.</p>						

